          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural rubidium target.",
                "About 1 mg/cm2 rubidium targets were prepared by",
                " vacuum evaporation of natural rubidium chloride on",
                " 7 mg/cm2 superpure Al backing.",
                "The target material was covered with a thin layer",
                " (100 ug/cm2) of Al coating to prevent the target from",
                " flaking out from the backing material.",
                "The target assembly consisted of a number of Rb",
                " targets sandwiched between Al degrader foils.",
                "The thickness of the degraders were adjusted so as to",
                " get the desired energy on different targets.",
                "The energy degradations were calculated using the",
                " stopping power data of Willlamson et al."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector resolution was found to be 2 keV",
                " at the 1333 keV 60Co peak.",
                "The detector efficiency was obtained from a set of",
                " calibration gamma-sources covering the region 122 to",
                " 1408 keV.",
                "Counting periods were varied between 100 sec and",
                " several hours depending on the activities and the",
                " half-lives of the isotopes being studied."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The duration of irradiations were between 10",
                " and 45 min and were adjusted according to the half-",
                " life of the nuclide of interest.",
                "The beam currents used in bombardments were around",
                " 700-800 nA.",
                "The flux of the beam passing through the target stack",
                " was measured in a Faraday cup.",
                "This was cross checked by using an aluminium monitor",
                " foil along with the target assembly."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "13-AL-27(A,X)11-NA-24,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "13-AL-27(A,X)11-NA-24,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "13-AL-27(A,X)11-NA-24",
                        "target": "13-AL-27",
                        "projectile": "A",
                        "process": "X",
                        "product": "11-NA-24",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The flux was cross checked by using an aluminium",
                " monitor foil along with the target assembly.",
                "The cross section for the production of 24Na from 27Al",
                " as a function of alpha-energy were taken from the",
                " tables of Martens and Schweimer"
              ]
            }
          ],
